Steps to check and run the commands of deployment in minikube

#To start Minikube
minikube start
#create the deployment file 
vi deployment.yml
#then run the command to start pod
#kubectl create -f deployment.yml
to check teh status 
#kubectl get pods
#kubectl get deployment
#to see the services
kubectl get svc
type should be node port to run the serrvices external
to get the url of the Pod
#minikube get svc < servicename>
To stop the deployement without deleteing it
kubectl scale deployment <deployment name> --replicas=0
to test it is working run this comamnd 
curl https://<node-port-ip>:8443
to get inside the conitaner which is created 
kubectl exec -it < deployement-name> -c < containername> -- /bin/bash
to get the container name 
kubectl get pods -o jsonpath="{.items[*].spec.containers[*].name}" or kubectl describe pod <podname>
to stop the minikube
minikube stop
